@startuml
!theme plain

title cloudsyncd pairing and protected download

actor "Browser user" as User
participant "Browser client\npublic/app.js" as Client
participant "Client API\nserver.js:21891" as API
database "data/state.json" as State
participant "shared/" as Shared

== PIN pairing ==
User -> Client : Enter 6-digit PIN
Client -> API : GET /api/pair/init
API --> Client : serverPublicKey
Client -> Client : Generate P-256 ECDH key pair\nHKDF(syncd-auth)\nHMAC(PIN)
Client -> API : POST /api/pair/verify\nclientPublicKey, proof, deviceId
API -> API : rate limit\nvalidate public key\ncompute shared secret
API -> State : store or update device
API --> Client : serverProof,\nencryptedMasterKey
Client -> Client : verify serverProof\nHKDF(syncd-transport)\ndecrypt masterKey\nsave IndexedDB

== File list ==
Client -> Client : derive request-auth key\nHMAC(method,path,timestamp,nonce,bodyHash)
Client -> API : GET /api/files\nX-Device-Id + HMAC headers
API -> API : timestamp window\nnonce replay check\nsignature check
API -> Shared : walkDir()
API --> Client : AES-GCM encrypted file tree
Client -> Client : decrypt and render list

== File download ==
Client -> Client : encode path segments\nsign request
Client -> API : GET /api/files/{path}\nX-Device-Id + HMAC headers
API -> API : auth check\nrealpath containment check
API -> Shared : fs.createReadStream(realFile)
API -> API : file -> AES-GCM cipher\nappend auth tag via pipeline
API --> Client : encrypted stream\nX-Encrypted-IV + tag length
Client -> Client : decrypt stream payload\nsave Blob download

@enduml
